The paper focuses on the convergence analysis of gradient-based meta-learning algorithms, which are commonly used in machine learning and optimization problems. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.CV (Computer Vision) since these fields heavily rely on meta-learning techniques. Additionally, the paper discusses the computational complexity and optimization of non-convex loss functions, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) and cs.SY (Systems and Control).
